This paper deals with the secrecy capacity of a wireless communication channel, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas at the transmitter and receiver also suggests that this paper could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on developing an achievable scheme and upper bound for the secrecy capacity suggests that this paper could also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
